    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. BURGESS:H.R. 5510.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:The attached language falls within Congress' enumeratedauthority to legislate interstate commerce, found in ArticleI, Section 8, clause 3 of the U.S. Constitution. Further,Article I, Section 1, of the Constitution establishes that``[a]ll legislative Powers herein granted shall be vested in. . . Congress. . . .'' This provision stands for theproposition that Congress sets the scope of agencies'authority to regulate and authorized Congress to set theinitial scope of the Federal Trade Commission's authority.[Page H3968]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
